SIMPLE: argus
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Argus
<hw>Ar"gus</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Argus</ets>, Gr. <?/.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Myth.)</fld> <def>A
fabulous being of antiquity, said to have had a hundred eyes, who has
placed by <persfn>Juno</persfn> to guard <persfn>Io</persfn>. His eyes
were transplanted to the peacock's tail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One very vigilant; a guardian always
watchful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of East Indian pheasants.
The common species (<spn>Argus giganteus</spn>) is remarkable for the
great length and beauty of the wing and tail feathers of the male. The
species <spn>Argus Grayi</spn> inhabits <geog>Borneo</geog>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Argus-eyed</ent>⟦br⟧
